BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Pen America": "https://pen.org/event/surveillance-on-the-quad/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:pen_america
SUMMARY:Surveillance on the Quad: Privacy\, Safety\, and Protest
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260416T150000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260416T150000
UID:8ad6dfca96b7e5d1a83699359f4b4a4e@pen.org
DESCRIPTION:Campus protest activity in recent years has coincided with an 
 increase in surveillance of students via campus police\, facilities manage
 ment\, and technology policies. Some argue that this is necessary to respo
 nd to criminal conduct such as vandalism and to support student safety. Ot
 hers allege that increased monitoring leads to a deep chilling of protecte
 d expression\, especially given how easy social media makes it to record a
 nd expose student demonstrators. Join a panel of experts to explore the ch
 allenges in navigating digital spaces\, student safety\, free expression\,
  and civil rights from theoretical and practical perspectives.\nRegister h
 ere
URL:https://pen.org/event/surveillance-on-the-quad/
X-SOURCE:PEN America
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Pen America": "https://pen.org/event/temple-beth-sholom-the-librarians/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:pen_america
SUMMARY:Temple Beth Sholom Presents: The Librarians
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260416T180000
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260416T180000
UID:508115e2c3b3acae120efeea9972d806@pen.org
DESCRIPTION:Cost: 15\nJoin Temple Beth Sholom for a special fundraising sc
 reening benefiting PEN America Florida and the Freedom to Read Project. Th
 e evening features\nThe Librarians\n\, from celebrated director\nKim A. Sn
 yder\nand executive producer\nSarah Jessica Parker.\nThe Librarians\ntells
  the harrowing story of librarians on the front lines of the book-ban cris
 is across the country. With stories from Florida\, Texas\, Louisiana\, and
  New Jersey\, the documentary traces the real-world impact of book bans on
  students\, educators\, librarians\, and families.\nFlorida is at the cent
 er of this fight. During the\n2024–2025 school year\, PEN America docume
 nted 2\,304 instances of book bans in the state\n. This film offers a chan
 ce to better understand what is happening in Florida and in communities ac
 ross the country.\nProceeds from ticket sales will go to PEN America Flori
 da and the Freedom to Read Project\, two Florida-based nonprofits dedicate
 d to fighting for the freedom to read.
LOCATION:Miami
URL:https://pen.org/event/temple-beth-sholom-the-librarians/
X-SOURCE:PEN America
END:VEVENT
