DTSTAMP:20260325T222302
CREATED:20260226T160353Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260325T172120Z
UID:70005-1778025600-1778371199@sabew.org
SUMMARY:2026 American health care: It’s becoming less affordable\, but will AI help improve the outcomes? fellowship program
DESCRIPTION:Apply for a fellowship to attend the “American health care: It’s becoming less affordable\, but will AI help improve the outcomes?” training in Philadelphia\, May 6-9\, 2026. Journalists selected will attend sessions covering topics about AI at the bedside and understanding AI’s profit in health care. In addition\, fellows will have the opportunity to attend other health care and business sessions during the 2026 SABEW Conference\, as well as participate in networking opportunities. \nThe fellows will take part in a field trip on Thursday morning\, May 7 and then enjoy a welcome & networking lunch upon their return to the hotel. Health care sessions will take place throughout the 2026 SABEW conference\, which runs Thursday afternoon\, May 7\, through Saturday\, May 9\, at 12:30 p.m. Fellows\, except those local to Philadelphia\, will be provided three nights of lodging at the DoubleTree Philadelphia Center City. Small travel stipends may be available for those not local to the area. \nTo apply for this program\, please submit an application here by Monday\, March 30 at 5 p.m. ET. To be considered for a fellowship\, you must have an active SABEW membership through June 1\, 2026. \nThe workshop is in partnership with the National Institute for Health Care Management (NIHCM) Foundation. \nIf you have any questions\, email logistics@sabew.org. \n  \n 
URL:https://sabew.org/event/2026-american-healthcare-its-becoming-less-affordable-but-will-ai-help-improve-the-outcomes-fellowship-program/
CATEGORIES:Fellowship,In-Person Training,Networking
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://sabew.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/NICHM-Fellowship-2026-Graphic-2-1.png
END:VEVENT
