DESCRIPTION:<h4>Start: <span style="font-weight: normal\;">Saturday\, May 1
 8\, 2026•07:00 PM</span></h4><h4>Location: <span style="font-weight: normal
 \;">Brooklyn Public Library Williamsburg • 240 Division Ave.\, at Marcy Ave
 \, New York\, NY 11211 US</span><br><br>Zohran Mamdani’s election as mayor 
 proved that New Yorkers can work together and win against impossible odds. 
 <span style="font-weight: normal\;">He successfully campaigned on a message
  of an affordable city that workers in New York deserve. To realize that vi
 sion\, we’ve got to keep organizing not just with our neighbors but also in
  our workplaces.</span><br><br><a href="https://workerorganizing.org/traini
 ng/nyc/#form"><u><u>We can win together. Sign up today.</u></u></a></h4><h4
 ><br><p><span style="font-weight: normal\;">EWOC will help you build the sk
 ills and give you the resources you and your co-workers need to demand what
  you deserve.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: normal\;">RSVP for our
  “Unite &amp\; Win at Work” training below. Food service workers\, warehous
 e workers\, office workers\, public-sector workers\, and anyone with a job 
 is welcome (except your boss).</span></p><p><span style="font-weight: norma
 l\;">An affordable New York means lower costs and more money in your wallet
 \, and it starts with talking with your co-workers.</span></p></h4>
